## 2026-05-15 ‚Äî "See all on the map" fix: listing_ids now populated in Mastra chat path

**Bug:** Clicking "See all on the map" from chat navigated to `/apartments?q=%7B%7D&view=map` with no `ids=` param ‚Äî showed all 44 apartments instead of the 5 returned by the AI.

**Root cause:** `normalizeToolOutput` (Mastra chat path) built `payload: { filters: {}, listings }` but never set `listing_ids`. `ChatActionBar` only adds `?ids=` when `listing_ids?.length > 0`, so the URL was missing that param and `useApartments` fetched everything.

**Fix:** One line in `normalizeToolOutput` ‚Äî extract IDs from the listings array and include them as `listing_ids`.

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `src/lib/chat/normalize-tool-output.ts` | **FIX** ‚Äî `normalizeToolOutput` now sets `listing_ids: listings.map(l => l.id)` in the returned payload; `ChatActionBar` will now set `?ids=<id1>,<id2>,...` and `useApartments` will filter to just those apartments |
| `src/lib/chat/normalize-tool-output.test.ts` | **+4 tests** ‚Äî `listing_ids` populated for rentals (3 IDs), events (2 IDs), empty array when no listings, order+count matches listings |

**Verified:** Live browser `import('/src/lib/chat/normalize-tool-output.ts')` ‚Üí `normalizeToolOutput('searchRentalsTool', [...])` returns `listing_ids: ['r-1','r-2','r-3']`. URL simulation produces `/apartments?q=%7B%7D&ids=r-1,r-2,...&view=map`. Map page at `?ids=...&view=map` renders the split-view and queries Supabase filtered to those IDs.

**Tests:** 211/211 ¬∑ **Lint:** 0 errors ¬∑ **Build:** exit 0 (7.7s)

