### PR #4 ‚Äî `c0d3764` ‚Äî Bug fix: auto-fire pending prompt waited for auth
**Production bug:** logged-out user typed prompt ‚Üí Google OAuth ‚Üí `/chat?send=pending` ‚Üí prompt was lost.

**Root cause:** ChatCanvas's auto-fire effect ran on first render. At that moment `useAuth.loading` was still `true` (Supabase establishing session post-OAuth) and `useAnonSession`'s effect hadn't fired (so `anonSessionId` was null). `sendMessage()` silent-returned (closure had `user=null && anonSessionId=null`), but we already cleared sessionStorage and locked the ref-guard. Net effect: prompt lost, URL clean, never re-fires.

**Fix:** added two new gates to the auto-fire effect:
```ts
if (authLoading) return;             // wait for Supabase session check
if (!user && !anonSessionId) return; // wait for anon session OR real user
```
And added `authLoading`, `user`, `anonSessionId` to the effect deps so it re-runs when auth settles. Imported `useAnonSession` directly in ChatCanvas (idempotent ‚Äî sessionStorage is the source of truth) so we can detect anon-session readiness from this component.

Edge cases preserved: StrictMode (ref-guard blocks 2nd pass), pasted `/chat?send=pending` URL in a new tab (lock ref + clean URL + no spurious sendMessage), email-confirmation link in a new tab (same path).

