  - **The big one.** Two independent Maps loaders (ChatMap inline bootstrap + GoogleMapView legacy `<script>`) were fighting over the same global, causing "API loaded multiple times" + every `<gmp-map>`/`<gmp-advanced-marker>` failing custom-element re-registration ‚Üí `gmp-advanced-marker-nondeterministic-duplicate1` deprecation warning. New `src/lib/google-maps-loader.ts` (271 lines, NEW) is the single source of truth. Idempotent across StrictMode + remounts. Detects pre-existing `<script id="google-maps-script">` and reuses it. Public API: `loadGoogleMapsLibrary(name, apiKey)`, `isMapsAuthFailed()`, `onMapsAuthFailed(cb)`. Both ChatMap and GoogleMapView migrated. `marker.addEventListener('gmp-click', ‚Ä¶)` + `gmpClickable: true`. Symmetric `removeEventListener` on unmount.
