  - **Quick Win #1**: `params.set('v', import.meta.env.PROD ? 'quarterly' : 'weekly')` ‚Äî tree-shake-verified; prod bundle only references the quarterly channel. Removes the #1 architectural risk (Google ships breaking changes weekly).
  - **Quick Win #4**: new `useEffect` keyed on `currentConversation?.id` calls `clearPins()` on every conversation switch. No more pin bleed across conversations.
  - **Quick Win #5**: `role="button"`, `aria-label="Open <title>, <label>"`, `aria-current="true"` on the highlighted pin, `aria-hidden` on the decorative emoji.
- **`b054b08`** `feat(maps): add pluggable telemetry hooks`
  - **Quick Win #2**: new `src/lib/maps-telemetry.ts`. 9 discriminated-union event kinds (`script_loaded`, `script_load_failed`, `auth_failed`, `map_init_failed`, `markers_rendered`, `marker_render_failed`, `pin_click`, `fitbounds`, `viewport_idle`, `cluster_expand`). Default sink is structured `console.error`/`console.debug`. Replace once at app boot to forward to Sentry/PostHog: `setMapTelemetrySink((event) => { Sentry.addBreadcrumb({...}); posthog.capture(...); })`. Resilience: `trackMapEvent` swallows sink throws ‚Äî telemetry must never break the app. **4/4 unit tests** (Vitest with mocked sink). `pin_click` events carry `viaKeyboard` and `newTab` flags, so we'll be able to see Cmd-click and Enter/Space conversions distinctly once a real sink is wired.
